      • registerSubclass

        public static void registerSubclass(java.lang.Class<? extends EquilibreObject> subclass)
        Registers a custom subclass type with the Equilibre Library, enabling strong-typing of those EquilibreObjects whenever they appear. Subclasses must specify the EquilibreClassName annotation and have a default constructor.
        Parameters:
        subclass - The subclass type to register.

      • saveAll

        public static <T extends EquilibreObject> void saveAll(java.util.List<T> objects)
                                                throws EquilibreException
        Saves each object in the provided list. This is faster than saving each object individually because it batches the requests.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the EquilibreObject's subclass
        Parameters:
        objects - The objects to save.
        Throws:
        EquilibreException - Throws an exception if the server returns an error or is inaccessible.

      • saveAllInBackground

        public static <T extends EquilibreObject> void saveAllInBackground(java.util.List<T> objects,
                                                                   SaveCallback callback)
        Saves each object in the provided list to the server in a background thread. This is preferable to using saveAll, unless your code is already running from a background thread.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the EquilibreObject's subclass
        Parameters:
        objects - The objects to save.
        callback - callback.done(e) is called when the save completes.

      • saveAllInBackground

        public static <T extends EquilibreObject> <any> saveAllInBackground(java.util.List<T> objects)
        Saves each object in the provided list to the server in a background thread. This is preferable to using saveAll, unless your code is already running from a background thread.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the EquilibreObject's subclass
        Parameters:
        objects - The objects to save.
        Returns:
        A task that is resolved when saveAll completes.
